list.item:
Octagon, the forthcoming Roosevelt–Churchill
                        conference; the Second Quebec Conference, September 11–16, 1944; Quebec;
                        short form for Octagon-out

div.p:
S—Mr. Secretary: At the request of the President, Mr. Harry Hopkins has called together several advisers to the Secretaries of the State, War and Treasury [Departments] for an exchange of views prior to a meeting of the three Secretaries to discuss the treatment of Germany. Three meetings were held over the weekend in which the following participated:
Messrs. Dunn, Matthews and Riddleberger for the State Department;
Mr. McCloy and General Hilldring for the War Department;
Dr. Harry White for the Treasury Department.

